snippet.textDisplay:
Let me explain the different types of hate in the WWE.
1. Hate because you suck at your job (e.g. Corbin)
2. Hate because you are a good heel (e.g. Bray Wyatt and Samoa Joe).
For the latter, these days true heels are cheered because we appreciate their work more. It doesn't mean we want them as face.
Me personally I was upset when the Miz turned face.. because it doesn't suit him. His personality is not designed to be a face.
I will cheer heel miz, but will boo face miz because of their job.
Similarly AJ Styles, Shinsuke Nakamura, and Sami Zayn are all people who should have never been heels. It screwed up their carears.
You should never just 'turn' for the sake of turning.
Seth Rollins recent heel turn was great. It made sense.. it wasn't out of the blue like some schizophrenic heel turn (e.g. Daniel Bryan or Big Shows 20000th heel turn)

snippet.textDisplay: Lol Vince and his Minions still thinking that 1980's Mentality still gets Over in almost 2020. Cheer the Good Guy, Boo the Bad Guy. RESPECT is how Every Wrestler Gets Over. They either like your Character, Moveset and Evolution or they Don't, You Earn Respect Over Time. You can be Cheered as a Bad Guy or Booed as a Good Guy, The Fans are Not saying to Change the Character, they are saying that him being a Good Guy Heel Best Suits his Character. Fans of Wrestling pick a Certain Group of Wrestlers that they think should be put in Each Catagory that should be Pushed and Promoted. Unfortunately Vince and the WWE also choose their Favorites. And they Control Everything so it's the Fans Job to Voice Distain for the Current Direction of Whomever gets Pushed that Might Not Deserve or Fit that Mold as Well as another less Promoted Wrestler. They Also get guys Over that otherwise wouldn't get over Relying on Vince and the WWE. Yes! There are the People's Champions that the Fans want and then there are the Corperate Champions that the Office wants to Push. Sometimes you get a Hybrid but Mostly you get Vince Killing an Organic Rise of a People's Champion by pushing his as a Corperate Champion ie Roman Reigns  After The Shield Split he should have left Reigns Alone with the USO's instead he tried to Push him Down the Fans Throats UnOrganically as the Replacement Superhero Character, He would have Risen on his Own. Btw Unless your Segment gets Over in the Ratings, Being Compared to Vicky Guererro is Not a Good Thing. She Ruined the Later half of Edge's Career, I couldn't even watch SmackDown cause she was So Annoying. Not Great Heel Annoying, X-Pac Go the Hell Away and get off My TV I am Changing the Channel until you Leave, I Don't Like You, You Suck Heat. Ask AEW fans if Vicky Gurerro should come over, The Ratings will Drop to an All Time Low until she gets Fired.

snippet.textDisplay:
You know, the sad fact is that there are those who take what they see a little 'too' far, not realizing that it's just a show, and that the WWE (much less 'any' wrestling promotion) isn't REAL. The idea that Baron Corbin has gotten death threats is absolutely ignorant, and those who would post such threats need to take a step back from the TV, go outside, and interact with reality.


I have been a UNDERTAKER fan since day one (1990), but I do NOT believe that a person can appear & disappear in the middle of the ring, or survive being buried alive multiple times. Taker is merely a 'character', nothing more. Baron Corbin plays a heel as part of his 'character', but at the end of the day, he is a HUMAN BEING.

I am a BARON CORBIN FAN.
